This paper discusses neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of different model structures such as Transformer and RNN, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The analysis of language characteristics also involves statistical modeling and data analysis, which are common in machine learning and statistical learning research, making cs.LG another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of sequence generation tasks such as text summarization, which falls under the category of neural networks (NE) and computer vision (CV), making these two sub-categories also possible.
